3 kinds of CSS.
Internal style sheets: in <style> </style>
External style sheets: a more realistic way to style your web pages and it's easier to read and manage your CSS
Inline

<!doctype html>

<html>

<head> 

<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="external style sheet.css">

</head>

<body>
 
<h1> The Fish Web Site </h1>

<p class="blue underline"> Welcome to the Fish Web Site. Everything you want to know about fish is in this web site. </p>
   
<h2> This is a section on Bass fish </h2>
   
<p class="purple"> Bass fish live in lakes. </p>

    <blockquote class="blue underline">

        This is an indent

    </blockquote>

</body>

</html>



notes: 
<link rel="" type="" href="xxx.css">: href points to where your external CSS is.
External style sheet saves as xxx.css
*Put these files in the same folder.
